Inside, enthusiastic recruiters engage with students, showcasing demo screens of the latest apps and glossy case study booklets. Students actively participate in a password cracking challenge organized by a cybersecurity company on laptops, clutching resumes in branded folders and utilizing tablets at kiosks to upload their resumes to the fair database. Concurrent workshops on networking etiquette, an alumni panel discussing technical interview preparations, and a lunchtime pitch session hosted by a startup founder occur in an adjoining classroom, with career counselors offering advice on applicable industries and visa sponsorship requirements. The inviting atmosphere is filled with the aromas of coffee and catered snacks. As the event concludes, students exit with tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, business cards, and resumes.

A cybersecurity company hosts a password cracking challenge on laptops, while students engage in uploading their resumes to the fair database at kiosks, rehearsing elevator pitches against the wall. Concurrent workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing technical interview preparations occur in an adjoining classroom. The lively atmosphere, enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks, sees students exit with tote bags filled with branded materials, including notebooks and business cards. A robotics startup attracts attention by flying a small drone above its booth, while volunteers collect leftover brochures.

Concurrent workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing interview preparations occur in an adjoining classroom. The atmosphere is lively, enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks in the lounge, where recruiters encourage students to follow up with personalized emails. As the event concludes, students exit with tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, business cards, and resumes, marking their target employers on the event map.

Students actively participate in a password cracking challenge organized by a cybersecurity company while small groups rehearse elevator pitches and identify target employers using an event map. They also queue for visa sponsorship advice, clutching resumes in branded folders. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, and business cards. Concurrent workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel occur in an adjoining classroom, alongside a lunchtime pitch session hosted by a startup founder. The aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts through the lounge, and as the final hour approaches, announcement chimes signal the end of the event, with students exiting while clutching tote bags and stacks of business cards.

Students engage in a password cracking challenge run by a cybersecurity company and utilize kiosks to upload their resumes to the fair database. Concurrent workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing preparations for technical interviews are conducted in an adjoining classroom. The aroma of coffee and catered snacks fills the air, while a robotics startup attracts attention by flying a small drone above its booth. As the event concludes, students exit with tote bags filled with business cards, resumes, branded notebooks, and pens, enjoying their haul while volunteers stack collapsed booths.

Volunteers gather leftover brochures, and university media teams capture interviews of attendees.
